results.overview: Two leading computer scientists work toward their goal of Technological Singularity,  as a radical anti-technology organization fights to prevent them from creating a world where computers can transcend the abilities of the human brain.
results.title: Transcendence

results.overview: This underground classic is considered by many to be Absinthe Films' greatest work to date. Transcendence marks the beginning of new kind of snowboarding film.
results.title: Transcendence

results.overview: Jeremiah awakens in a river with no memory. With the help of clinically depressed psychologist Alex Cohen, they begin to unravel the dark mysteries of Jeremiah's identity.
results.title: Transcendence

results.original_title: Bob Birdnow's Remarkable Tale of Human Survival and the Transcendence of Self
results.overview: When invited by an old friend to speak to a struggling sales team at a conference, Bob Birdnow reluctantly agrees. Bob's attempt to say something motivational takes an unexpected turn when, forced off script and desperate, he begins the one story he'd hoped he'd never have to tell.
results.title: Bob Birdnow's Remarkable Tale of Human Survival and the Transcendence of Self

results.overview: The compelling feature-length documentary film, by director Barry Ptolemy, chronicles the life and controversial ideas of luminary Ray Kurzweil. For more than three decades, inventor, futures, and New York Times best-selling author Ray Kurzweil has been one of the most respected and provocative advocates of the role of technology in our future.
results.title: Transcendent Man

results.overview: OVA following the quirky adventures of the immaculate Shoko Asahara.
results.title: Transcendent World

results.overview: Documentary short about the contrasting experiences, past and present, of three trans men of different generations.
results.title: Transcender

results.overview: The extraordinary journey of a transgender named Pradeep Kumar who became Prithika Yashini, who fights hard against gender discrimination to become India's first transwoman.
results.title: Transcender

results.overview: TRANSCENDENT is a short film inspired by the visionary writings of horror author H.P. Lovecraft. Following one woman's journey to find her true place in the world; TRANSCENDENT is a different kind of 'Homecoming' story loosely adapted from Lovecraft's 'The Shadow Over Innsmouth'. It lives somewhere between art film, surrealist experiment, and horror film.
results.title: Transcendent

results.overview: Two Native Americans struggle to make the transition from their home reservation to the city life, but soon find a solution in an advertised remedy that promises to transform their primitive behavior, to the ranks of the refined and successful.
results.title: The Transcenders

results.overview: Roger, a Rasputin-like drifter, is in search of the ultimate indie-rock band, The Transcendents. What he finds is less than transcendent: a band who has all but abandoned society, a host of unpleasant memories, and more questions than answers in search of his own existential fulfillment. Set in the Wonderland of America's Do-it-Yourself music scene, The Transcendents is a dark comedic fairytale that straddles the line between the absurd and the all too real.
results.title: The Transcendents

results.overview: A unique and personal register of the trip American director David Lynch did to Brazil to divulge Transcendental Meditation and launch a book on the subject. His intimacy with the camera, generosity and patience with fans and admirers - that treat him like a rock star - and his reluctance to talk about his films, reveal the man usually behind dark film scenes in a unique and very personal way. The films reveals Lynch's peculiar sense of humor and his faith on the benefits TM can bring everywhere, especially to regions and countries suffocated by violence and social instability.
results.title: Transcendendo Lynch

results.overview: John Gage loves Ruth West, but she marries his friend, Charles Grey. The young couple are apparently happy; a child is born to them. Suddenly Ruth discovers that her husband has been systematically robbing his employer. Threatened with imprisonment unless he refunds the money he has stolen, Grey is at his wits' end.
results.title: The Love Transcendent

results.overview: Brian, a stand-up comedian whose life is spinning out of control, has to deal with kidnap, then escapes and had to search for his would-be murderer who has ordered the kidnap.
results.title: Transcendental Layover

results.original_title: The Transcendental Object at the End of Time
results.overview: An audio-visual journey through the mind of Terence McKenna.
results.title: The Transcendental Object at the End of Time

results.overview: Transcendental Blues is an album released in 2000 by Steve Earle. It features Sharon Shannon on the track "The Galway Girl". The album was nominated for a Grammy in the Best Contemporary Folk Album category.
results.title: Steve Earle Transcendental Blues Live
